---
import SiteLayout from '@/layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---
<SiteLayout title="Work" description="Practical AI workshops and agentic engineering enablement with Sasha Vinčić.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-5 py-20 md:py-28">
    <p class="mb-5 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-base-500">Work</p>
    <h1 class="max-w-4xl font-serif text-6xl font-light leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-7xl">Practical AI workshops for software teams.</h1>
    <p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-8 text-base-650">I help teams move from prompting experiments to agentic engineering workflows they can actually use.</p>
    <p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl leading-7 text-base-650">These workshops are not generic ChatGPT training. My deepest work is with software teams and technical leaders: code, repositories, review, testing, documentation, workflow design, and guardrails.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-5 py-12 border-t border-base-200">
    <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="border-t border-base-300 pt-6">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-light">For software teams</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">Agentic coding workflows, code review, tests, documentation, delivery, context management, and the guardrails that keep AI useful instead of theatrical.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="border-t border-base-300 pt-6">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-light">For business teams</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">I also run practical AI workshops for marketing, HR/PX, sales, and leadership teams when the goal is to improve real work.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="border-t border-base-300 pt-6">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-light">The common principle</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">The examples change. The principle does not: less AI theatre, more useful workflows, better judgement, and Monday-morning changes.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-5 py-14 border-t border-base-200">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-5xl font-light tracking-tight">Formats</h2>
    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="bg-base-50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-base-500">45–90 minutes</p>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-light">Talk / keynote</h3>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">For leadership groups, engineering orgs, and internal inspiration days. Shared vocabulary and realistic expectations.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="bg-base-50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-base-500">Half day</p>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-light">Practical workshop</h3>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">Hands-on work with concrete AI workflows, code/review/tests/docs where relevant, and team-specific guardrails.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="bg-base-50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-base-500">1–2 weeks</p>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-light">Enablement sprint</h3>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">For teams ready to change how they work. We design and test real workflows in your repo, tooling, and team context.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-12"><a href="/contact/" class="rounded-full bg-base-950 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-base-800">Talk to me about a workshop</a></p>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
